de.stroeer.proxity.gateway

Interface Gateway.IGatewayListener

  • Enclosing class:
    Gateway

    public static interface Gateway.IGatewayListener
    This class is the information interface between app and sdk. Every change in status and event which occurs inside of the sdk will be notified on this Listener.
    The different types of information are separated in three methods:
    Each time a specific status was gained (for example: Bluetooth enabled, Internet connection available) you will be notified via onStatusGained(Dependencies, boolean) .
    Each time a status is revoked, the onStatusRevoked(Dependencies, boolean) will be called.
    If there is any message(for example: Created new User, download of data finished) or new data which should be sent to the app the onMessage(Message, boolean) will be called.

      • onMessage

        void onMessage(Message message,
               boolean deliverdForFirstTime)
        This method is called whenever the sdk has to inform you about new messages.
        Parameters:
        message: - the message with description, code and data
        deliverdForFirstTime: - determines if this message was sent for the first time (true) or it is a copy (false). This is necessary for resetting the app if its gone to background and was brought to the front again.
